main event: A cylindrical object was observed hovering over Cerro Catalan, Uruguay on May 4, 1958.
interesting points: The object remained stationary for 6 minutes, accompanied by a slow pulsing noise when it moved.
The object had a cylindrical shape, was white in color, and had no visible wings.
The object performed rapid vertical maneuvers relative to the horizon.
Other similar sightings were reported in Uruguay during the second quarter of 1956.
The case was compared to a 1948 incident where a large unidentified object was encountered by a DC-3 aircraft near Atlanta, Georgia.
